The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing dynamic networks from heterogeneous datasets, which involves statistical inference and machine learning techniques. The paper uses ARMAX models to parametrize linear network models, which is a common approach in system identification and control theory. The paper also introduces and extends several methods for group sparse estimation, which is a popular technique in network inference and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Statistical Machine Learning), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the analysis of network structure and dynamics, which suggests the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as possible choices.
